# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Step-by-step Deobfuscation

The code uses a common JavaScript obfuscation pattern:
1. **String array** (`a0_0x4453`) — holds base64-encoded strings
2. **Decoder function** (`a0_0x305b`) — decodes base64 strings with a lookup cache
3. **Array shuffler** (the IIFE) — rotates the string array until a checksum matches
4. **Obfuscated variable/property names** — all meaningful names are replaced with hex identifiers

## Deobfuscated Code

```javascript
// Constants
const TAU = 6.283;          // ~2π
const PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
const SQRT1_2 = 0.707;      // ~√(1/2)

// Physics/simulation configuration
const config = {
    repulsionStrength: 4000,
    frictionCoeff: 0.004,
    amplitudeDamping: 0.92,
    dispersal: 0.0003,
    streamMax: 40,
    gravityDecay: 0.04,
    lerp: 0.06
};

// ========== NODES (graph vertices) ==========
const nodes = [
    { id: "hub",     label: "Hub",     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// ========== EDGES (spring connections) ==========
const edges = [
    { a: "hub",   b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera state (with lerp smoothing)
let camera       = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
let cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle stream
let particles = [];
let frameCount = 0;

// ========== Helper: find node by ID ==========
function findNode(id) {
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// ========== PHYSICS: Apply forces ==========
function applyForces() {
    // 1. Node-to-node REPULSION (Coulomb-like)
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            let dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            let dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            let force = config.repulsionStrength / (dist * dist);
            let fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            let fy = (dy / dist) * force;

            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2. Edge SPRING forces (Hooke's law)
    for (let i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        let nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
        let nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        let dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        let dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        let displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
        let force = (edges[i].k || config.frictionCoeff) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3. CENTER GRAVITY + DAMPING + position integration
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        // Gentle pull toward center (400, 300)
        nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.dispersal;
        nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.dispersal;

        // Velocity damping
        nodes[i].vx *= config.amplitudeDamping;
        nodes[i].vy *= config.amplitudeDamping;

        // Euler integration
        nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
        nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
    }
}

// ========== PARTICLES: Spawn ==========
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.streamMax) return;

    // Pick a random node as origin
    let origin = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    let angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    let speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;

    particles.push({
        x: origin.x,
        y: origin.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT1_2
    });
}

// ========== PARTICLES: Update ==========
function updateParticles() {
    for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        let p = particles[i];

        // Friction/drag on particle velocity
        p.vx *= 1 - config.gravityDecay * 0.125;
        p.vy *= 1 - config.gravityDecay * 0.125;

        // Move
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;

        // Age and remove expired
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(i, 1);
        }
    }
}

// ========== CAMERA: Smooth lerp ==========
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x    += (cameraTarget.x    - camera.x)    * config.lerp;
    camera.y    += (cameraTarget.y    - camera.y)    * config.lerp;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom)  * config.lerp;
}

// ========== MAIN LOOP ==========
function tick() {
    applyForces();        // Physics step
    frameCount++;
    updateParticles();    // Move/cull particles
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();  // Spawn every 3rd frame
    updateCamera();       // Smooth camera
}

setInterval(tick, 16);    // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** — the same kind of layout algorithm used in tools like D3.js, Gephi, or network visualizers:

### Core Mechanics

| Component | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| **Repulsion** | All nodes push each other apart (inverse-square law, like electric charges) |
| **Springs** | Connected nodes are pulled together by Hooke's law toward a rest length |
| **Center gravity** | A weak force pulls everything toward (400, 300) so the graph doesn't drift away |
| **Damping** | Velocity is multiplied by 0.92 each frame to prevent infinite oscillation |
| **Particles** | Decorative particles spawn from random nodes, drift outward, and fade/die after a random lifespan |
| **Camera** | A virtual camera smoothly interpolates (lerps) toward a target position/zoom |

### The Graph Structure

```
        epsilon
          |
    gamma --- alpha
      \      / |
       \    /  |
        hub    |
       / \     |
      /   \    |
   beta    delta
```

A central **Hub** node (largest, r=26) connects to 5 satellite nodes, with a few cross-connections between satellites. This creates a classic **hub-and-spoke network topology** that the force simulation arranges into a visually balanced layout.

### Summary
> **It's a headless (no rendering code) force-directed graph physics engine with decorative particle effects and smooth camera movement, running at ~60 FPS.** The rendering/drawing code is presumably elsewhere.
